  "texts": [
    "The susceptible genotypes were as follows: (Guiana) ELP 37A, GU 123 V, GU 195 V, and Ker 6; (Iquitos) Amaz 12, IMC 105, IMC 31, IMC 57; (Marañón) PA 107, PA 299, PA 81, and PA 71; (Nanay) NA 70, NA 807, NA 33, and NA 34.To investigate how divergence among populations affects the evolution of cacao's defense response, and to discover potentially novel mechanisms underlying defense to P. palmivora, we performed an RNA-seq experiment.",
    "We began by importing 31 genotypes as grafted plants from the ex situ International Cocoa Collection (IC3) at the Tropical Agricultural Research and Higher Education Center (CATIE), Costa Rica.",
    "Approximately 300 cuttings were taken from these grafted plants, of which 141 rooted plants survived, representing 27 genotypes.",
    "The healthy plants were established in the greenhouse at Penn State University (Additional file 1: Table S12).",
    "To minimize the effects of greenhouse gradients in temperature, humidity, and other abiotic factors, 6-week-old plants were distributed across the greenhouse in a pseudo-randomized block design (Additional file 2: Fig."
